oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Martha Bittinger
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Martha Bittinger, daughter of Mr. & Mrs. Frank Bittinger, Kingston Springs, Tennessee, proudly exhibits a small section of their home food supply pantry. She is wearing a dress with a matching belt and her hand is resting on a jar.
The Home Food Supply Program was a war-relief program instituted by the administration of Gov. Prentice Cooper.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
